    "description": "If you're a passionate Quality Control Engineer with drive and ambition, Ambuja Cements Capital India in Dhanbad is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Ambuja Cements Capital India:\nAmbuja Cements Capital India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Manage raw material procurement and inventory levels\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Referral bonus program\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Dhanbad, Jharkhand, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Ambuja Cements Capital India!",
